### BPD Materials

**Access Restrictions:**
- **Department Restriction**: Users can only see BPD materials that belong to business plans in their assigned department (based on `users.department_id`)
- **Regional Restriction**: Users can only see BPD materials that belong to business plans in their allowed sub divisions (via `users_sd` table)
- Both restrictions are applied together - users must have access to both the department and sub-division to see a BPD material
- If a user has no allowed sub divisions, they will see no materials
- If there are no business plans in the user's allowed sub divisions and department, they will see no materials
- Super admin user (configurable via `SUPER_ADMIN_USER_ID` environment variable, default: 1) bypasses sub division filtering in queries, but still requires sub divisions to be assigned to see any materials

**Permission Note:**
- GET requests are allowed if the user has `show` permission on `materials-report` page OR `business-plans` page
- Non-GET methods (POST, PUT, DELETE) require `business-plans` page permissions
- Action endpoints (`/actions/allocate` and `/actions/use`) have separate permission requirements

#### GET /api/bpd-materials
Get all BPD materials with pagination.

**Headers:**
```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

**Query Parameters:**
- `page` (optional): Page number (default: 1)
- `limit` (optional): Items per page (default: 10)
- `sort_by` (optional): Sort field (default: bpdm_id). Valid fields: bpdm_id, bpd_id, m_id, r_qty, alloc_qty, status, act_qty
- `sort_order` (optional): Sort order - `asc` or `desc` (default: desc)
- `all` (optional): If `true`, returns all materials without pagination (requires `bpd_id` query param)
- `bpd_id` (optional): Filter materials by business plan detail ID

