#### GET /api/project-issues/:id
Get project issue by ID.

**Permission Note:**
- This GET endpoint is allowed if the user has `show` permission on **ANY** of: `project-issues`, `project-issue-open`, or `project-issue-complete`.
- This allows users who can perform actions on project issues to view them, even if they don't have full `project-issues` page permissions.

**Headers:**
```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

**Response:**
The response includes `opened_at` (timestamp when the issue was opened/created), `completed_at` (timestamp when the issue was completed, null if not completed), `updated_by` (user ID), and `updated_by_username` (username of the user who last updated the project issue) fields, along with related `issue` and `business_plan` objects.

**Note:**
- `opened_at` is automatically set to the current timestamp when the project issue is created
- `completed_at` is automatically set to the current timestamp when the project issue status changes to 2 (completed)
- These fields are read-only and cannot be set via API requests

#### PUT /api/project-issues/:id
Update project issue.

**Headers:**
```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "issue_id": 2,
  "proj_id": 1,
  "description": "Updated issue description",
  "remarks_3": "Additional notes"
}
```

**Field Constraints:**
- `issue_id`: Must reference an existing issue
- `proj_id`: Must reference an existing business plan
- `description`: Description of the project issue (nullable) - can be updated through this endpoint
- `remarks_1`: Opening remarks (nullable) - can be updated through this endpoint, but only when issue status is 0 (open)
- `remarks_3`: Completed remarks (nullable) - can be updated through this endpoint, but only when issue status is 2 (completed)

**Note:** All fields are optional. Only include fields you want to update. The `updated_by` field is automatically set to the ID of the authenticated user making the request, and `updated_at` is automatically updated.
- **Status cannot be updated through this endpoint.** Use the action endpoint instead:
  - `PUT /api/project-issues/:id/actions/complete` - to complete an issue (status 0 → 2)
- **remarks_1 can be updated through this endpoint, but only when issue status is 0 (open).** It can also be set when opening an issue via the open action endpoint.
- **remarks_3 can be updated through this endpoint, but only when issue status is 2 (completed).** It can also be set when completing an issue via the complete action endpoint.

**Response:**
The response includes `updated_by` (user ID) and `updated_by_username` (username of the user who last updated the project issue) fields.

**Error Responses:**
- `400` - Invalid project issue ID
- `400` - Status cannot be updated through this endpoint. Use the action endpoints instead.
- `400` - remarks_1 can only be updated when issue status is 0 (open). Current status is X.
- `400` - remarks_3 can only be updated when issue status is 2 (completed). Current status is X.
- `400` - Invalid Issue ID or Project ID
- `404` - Project issue not found

#### PUT /api/project-issues/:id/actions/complete
Complete a project issue (change status from 0 to 2). This endpoint requires separate permissions on the "Project Issue Complete" page.

**Headers:**
```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "remarks_3": "Optional remarks when completing this issue"
}
```

**Note:** 
- Request body is optional
- Changes status from 0 (open) to 2 (completed)
- Only issues with status 0 can be completed
- `remarks_3` (optional): Remarks to add when completing the issue. `remarks_3` can also be updated later through the standard edit endpoint when issue status is 2 (completed).
- `completed_at` is automatically set to the current timestamp when the issue is completed
- This endpoint requires `edit` permission on the `project-issue-complete` page (separate from the `project-issues` page)

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Project issue completed successfully",
  "data": {
    "pi_id": 1,
    "issue_id": 1,
    "proj_id": 1,
    "status": 2,
    "description": "Issue description here",
    "remarks_1": null,
    "remarks_2": null,
    "remarks_3": "Issue resolved successfully",
